SUMMARY:[Maine Secretary of State] Maine Secretary of State’s Office ann
 ounces recount schedule
DESCRIPTION:AUGUSTA\, MAINE\n– The Department of the Secretary of State 
 announced the schedule for recounts requested by candidates in three races
 :\nRecounts:\nMonday\, June 22 at 9 a.m.: Senate District 30 – Democrat\
 nThursday\, June 25 at 9 a.m.: House District 49 – Republican\nThursday\
 , June 25 at 1 p.m.: House District 135 – Democrat\nThe recounts will ta
 ke place in the Florian Room located at the Maine Public Safety Building a
 t 45 Commerce Ave.\, Augusta. Recounts are open to the public and media an
 d will be livestreamed on the Secretary of State’s\nYouTube page\n.\nAdd
 itional recounts could be requested following the conclusion of the ranked
  choice voting tabulations.\nRecount process:\nMaine statute\nTitle 21-A\,
  §737-A\nlays out a specific plan\, process and any related costs for vot
 es to be recounted. In a recount\, representatives of each candidate and s
 taff members from the Department of the Secretary of State manually review
  each paper ballot to determine the official vote tally:\nIn Ranked Choice
  Voting races\n: only a candidate who received one of the top three rankin
 gs at the end of the penultimate round of ranked‑choice counting may req
 uest a recount\, and they must file with the Secretary of State a written 
 request within five business days after results are announced.\nIn non-Ran
 ked Choice races:\nany candidate other than the apparent winner who desire
 s a recount must file with the Secretary of State a written request for a 
 recount within five business days after the election.\nOfficial results wi
 ll be available and posted within 20 days after the election on the\nElect
 ion Results page\n.\n###\nhttps://www.maine.gov/sos/news/maine-secretary-s
 tates-office-announces-recount-schedule
