SUMMARY:[Maine Secretary of State] Maine Secretary of State’s Office ann
 ounces additional races for Ranked Choice Voting tabulations\, recounts
DESCRIPTION:AUGUSTA\, MAINE\n– The Department of the Secretary of State 
 announced today two additional races will proceed to ranked choice voting 
 tabulation and three to recounts:\nRanked choice tabulation:\nHouse Distri
 ct 58 – Republican (Belgrade\, Fayette\, Rome\, Vienna\, Mount Vernon\, 
 New Sharon)\nSenate District 4 – Republican (Bradford\; Charleston\, Cor
 inna\, Corinth\, Dexter\, Exeter\, Garland\, Glenburn\, Hudson\, Kenduskea
 g\, Levant)\nGovernor – Democrat\nGovernor – Republican\nU.S. Congress
  CD2 – Democrat\nRecounts:\nSenate District 30 – Democrat (Gorham\, Sc
 arborough (part))\nHouse District 49 – Republican (Arrowsic\, Georgetown
 \, Phippsburg\, West Bath\, Woolwich)\nHouse District 135 – Democrat  (
 Kennebunk (part))\nThe ranked choice tabulation process began on Friday\, 
 June 12 at 1 PM at the Maine Department of Public Safety Headquarters buil
 ding located at 45 Commerce Drive in Augusta and is expected to conclude t
 his week. The ranked choice process is open to the public and media and is
  being livestreamed on the Secretary of State’s\nYouTube page\n. Recount
 s will begin next week with dates to be announced later this week.\nHow Ra
 nked Choice Voting works in Maine:\nIn Ranked Choice Voting races\, a cand
 idate must receive more than 50% of the first-choice votes as counted on E
 lection Day to win the race outright. If no candidate appears to have achi
 eved this based on initial unofficial results reports from the municipalit
 ies\, the Secretary of State’s Office makes the determination to proceed
  with the\nranked-choice voting tabulation\n. The votes are tabulated in 
 rounds\, with the lowest-ranked candidate eliminated in each round until t
 here are only two candidates remaining. The candidate determined to have r
 eceived the majority (more than 50%) of the votes in the final round is de
 clared the winner.  For more information about how ranked-choice races ar
 e tabulated\, visit the\nRCV Resources webpage\non the Secretary of State 
 website.\nRecount process:\nMaine statute\nTitle 21-A\, §737-A\nlays out 
 a specific plan\, \nhttps://www.maine.gov/sos/news/maine-secretary-states-
 office-announces-additional-races-ranked-choice-voting-tabulations
