 s\; Summer Flounder Fishery\; Quota Transfer From North Carolina to Virgin
 ia
DESCRIPTION:NMFS announces that the State of North Carolina is transferrin
 g a portion of its 2026 commercial summer flounder quota to the Commonweal
 th of Virginia. This adjustment to the 2026 fishing year quota is necessar
 y to comply with the Summer Flounder\, Scup\, and Black Sea Bass Fishery M
 anagement Plan (FMP) quota transfer provisions. This announcement informs 
 the public of the revised 2026 commercial quotas for North Carolina and Vi
 rginia.\nhttps://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2026/07/16/2026-14369/f
 isheries-of-the-northeastern-united-states-summer-flounder-fishery-quota-t
 ransfer-from-north
