SUMMARY:[Federal Maine-Related] Rescission of Climate-Related Disclosure R
 ules
DESCRIPTION:The Securities and Exchange Commission ("Commission") proposes
  to rescind amendments to its rules under the Securities Act of 1933 ("Sec
 urities Act") and Securities Exchange Act of 1934 ("Exchange Act") that re
 quire registrants to provide certain climate- related information in their
  registration statements and annual reports.\nhttps://www.federalregister.
 gov/documents/2026/06/03/2026-11091/rescission-of-climate-related-disclosu
 re-rules
URL:https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2026/06/03/2026-11091/rescis
 sion-of-climate-related-disclosure-rules
CATEGORIES:Federal Maine-Related
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:116d97ea9154d9fb@fed-register-maine.maine-government-feeds
DTSTAMP:20260701T202303Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
SUMMARY:[Federal Maine-Related] Board of Directors\; Request for Nomination
DESCRIPTION:The Unified Carrier Registration (UCR) Plan Board of Directors
  is requesting nominations of qualified individuals from each of the Feder
 al Motor Carrier Safety Administration's (FMCSA) four service areas (as th
 ose areas were defined by FMCSA on January 1\, 2005) for appointment by FM
 CSA to the UCR Plan Board of Directors. The nominees must be from among th
 e Chief Administrative Officers of State Agencies responsible for overseei
 ng the administration of the UCR Agreement. The selected individuals will 
 fill four vacancies for terms which begin immediately on appointment and e
 xpire on May 31\, 2029.\nhttps://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2026/06
 /01/2026-10909/board-of-directors-request-for-nomination
URL:https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2026/06/01/2026-10909/board-
 of-directors-request-for-nomination
CATEGORIES:Federal Maine-Related
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
