BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:0e93e699e47c8877@fed-cfpb-news.maine-government-feeds
DTSTAMP:20260705T190803Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20250711
SUMMARY:[Federal Practice Areas] CFPB Reaches Settlement with FirstCash\, 
 Inc. and Its Subsidiaries for Military Lending Act Violations
DESCRIPTION:Today\, in the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau’s (CFPB)
  November 12\, 2021 lawsuit against FirstCash\, Inc.\, and nineteen subsid
 iaries alleging violations of the Military Lending Act (MLA)\, the parties
  reached a settlement and jointly filed a stipulated final judgment and pr
 oposed order\, which if entered by the court\, would resolve the lawsuit.\
 nhttps://www.consumerfinance.gov/about-us/newsroom/cfpb-reaches-settlement
 -with-firstcash-inc-and-its-subsidiaries-for-military-lending-act-violatio
 ns/
URL:https://www.consumerfinance.gov/about-us/newsroom/cfpb-reaches-settlem
 ent-with-firstcash-inc-and-its-subsidiaries-for-military-lending-act-viola
 tions/
CATEGORIES:Federal Practice Areas
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:18cf9411aac8e934@fed-cfpb-news.maine-government-feeds
DTSTAMP:20260705T190803Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20250515
SUMMARY:[Federal Practice Areas] CFPB Amends Wise Order for Remittance Pra
 ctices
DESCRIPTION:The CFPB amended its January 30\, 2025 consent order with the 
 international remittance company Wise resolving claims including advertisi
 ng inaccurate fees and failing to properly disclose exchange rates and oth
 er costs.\nhttps://www.consumerfinance.gov/about-us/newsroom/cfpb-amends-w
 ise-order-for-remittance-practices/
URL:https://www.consumerfinance.gov/about-us/newsroom/cfpb-amends-wise-ord
 er-for-remittance-practices/
CATEGORIES:Federal Practice Areas
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:18e1f79502573fba@fed-cfpb-news.maine-government-feeds
DTSTAMP:20260705T190803Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20250506
SUMMARY:[Federal Practice Areas] CFPB Announcement Regarding Enforcement A
 ctions Related to Buy Now\, Pay Later Loans
DESCRIPTION:The CFPB is announcing that it will not prioritize enforcement
  actions taken on the basis of the Truth in Lending (Regulation Z)\; Use o
 f Digital User Accounts to Access Buy Now\, Pay Later Loans\, 89 Fed. Reg.
  47\,068 (May 31\, 2024) (“Buy Now\, Pay Later”).\nhttps://www.consume
 rfinance.gov/about-us/newsroom/cfpb-announcement-regarding-enforcement-act
 ions-related-to-buy-now-pay-later-loans/
URL:https://www.consumerfinance.gov/about-us/newsroom/cfpb-announcement-re
 garding-enforcement-actions-related-to-buy-now-pay-later-loans/
CATEGORIES:Federal Practice Areas
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:91eab785d17a9415@fed-cfpb-news.maine-government-feeds
DTSTAMP:20260705T190803Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20250430
SUMMARY:[Federal Practice Areas] CFPB Keeps Its Enforcement and Supervisio
 n Resources Focused on Pressing Threats to Consumers
DESCRIPTION:The CFPB is announcing that it will not prioritize enforcement
  or supervision actions with regard to entities that are currently outside
  the stay imposed under Texas Bankers Association v. CFPB\, No. 24-40705 (
 CA5).\nhttps://www.consumerfinance.gov/about-us/newsroom/cfpb-keeps-its-en
 forcement-and-supervision-resources-focused-on-pressing-threats-to-consume
 rs/
URL:https://www.consumerfinance.gov/about-us/newsroom/cfpb-keeps-its-enfor
 cement-and-supervision-resources-focused-on-pressing-threats-to-consumers/
CATEGORIES:Federal Practice Areas
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:36f6d77068b53ae0@fed-cfpb-news.maine-government-feeds
DTSTAMP:20260705T190803Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20250411
SUMMARY:[Federal Practice Areas] CFPB Offers Regulatory Relief From Regist
 ration Requirements for Small Loan Providers
DESCRIPTION:The Consumer Financial Protection Bureau will not prioritize e
 nforcement or supervision actions for entities that do not satisfy future 
 deadlines to submit registration information under the regulation titled "
 Registry of Nonbank Covered Persons Subject to Certain Agency and Court Or
 ders".\nhttps://www.consumerfinance.gov/about-us/newsroom/cfpb-offers-regu
 latory-relief-from-registration-requirements-for-small-loan-providers/
URL:https://www.consumerfinance.gov/about-us/newsroom/cfpb-offers-regulato
 ry-relief-from-registration-requirements-for-small-loan-providers/
CATEGORIES:Federal Practice Areas
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
